import seaborn as sns
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    ax = sns.barplot(x='job', y='count', data=data)
    plt.title('What is the distribution of job categories in the dataset?', wrap=True)
    plt.xticks(rotation=90)
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        ax.xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
chart.show()

import seaborn as sns
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    sns.barplot(x='job', y='count', hue='sex', data=data, ci=None)
    plt.title('What is the gender distribution across different job categories?', wrap=True)
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        plt.gca().xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
chart.show()

import seaborn as sns
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    job_perc = data.groupby('job')['job_perc'].sum().reset_index()
    plt.pie(job_perc['job_perc'], labels=job_perc['job'], autopct='%1.1f%%')
    plt.title('What is the percentage distribution of job categories?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
chart.show()
